parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, leading to costly repairs and potential environmental harm.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.
The failure of the transmission valve body assembly can cause rough shifting, leading to reduced vehicle performance and safety risks.
Water in the air filter can cause engine performance issues, reduced fuel efficiency, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Water found on the inside of the air filter

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power window slows down or stops moving while being operated
the power window gets stuck in a partially open or closed position
the power window requires multiple attempts to open or close
the power window motor makes unusual noises or produces excessive heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause a range of problems, including malfunctioning accessories, faulty lighting, and even engine stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake lights malfunction or fail to illuminate
electrical accessories such as power windows or locks malfunction
intermittent or complete loss of electrical power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially on highways or in remote areas.
symptoms: vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel pump/sensor unit can cause the fuel pump to short out electrically, leading to fuel tank damage, fuel leaks, and potentially, engine failure or fires.
